## 2. Option 1: Build with vcpkg (Recommended)
This is the preferred method for handling dependencies automatically.

@build_vcpkg_rules [
  {
    "id": "install_vcpkg",
    "rule": "Clone and bootstrap vcpkg using the provided commands.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": "git clone https://github.com/Microsoft/vcpkg.git\ncd vcpkg\n.\\bootstrap-vcpkg.bat"
  },
  {
    "id": "install_dependencies",
    "rule": "Install GLFW3 and GLEW via vcpkg for x64-windows.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": ".\\vcpkg\\vcpkg.exe install glfw3:x64-windows glew:x64-windows"
  },
  {
    "id": "build_project",
    "rule": "Use the build script or manual CMake commands with vcpkg toolchain.",
    "severity": "high",
    "example": ".\\build_with_vcpkg.bat\n# Or manually:\nmkdir build-vcpkg\ncd build-vcpkg\ncmake .. -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../vcpkg/scripts/buildsystems/vcpkg.cmake -G \"Visual Studio 17 2022\" -A x64\ncmake --build . --config Release"
  }
]

- Integrate with GitHub workflows using mcp_github_run_workflow for automated builds.

## 3. Option 2: Build with System Packages
Alternative method for manual dependency installation.

@build_system_packages_rules [
  {
    "id": "install_dependencies",
    "rule": "Manually install GLFW3 and GLEW on the system.",
    "severity": "medium"
  },
  {
    "id": "build_project",
    "rule": "Create build directory and run CMake without vcpkg.",
    "severity": "medium",
    "example": "mkdir build\ncd build\ncmake .. -G \"Visual Studio 17 2022\" -A x64\ncmake --build . --config Release"
  }
]

- Use mcp_github_search_* to find installation guides if needed.

## 4. Option 3: Use CMake Presets
Simplified configuration using presets.

@build_presets_rules [
  {
    "id": "configure_preset",
    "rule": "Configure with windows-vcpkg preset.",
    "severity": "medium",
    "example": "cmake --preset windows-vcpkg"
  },
  {
    "id": "build_preset",
    "rule": "Build using the preset.",
    "severity": "medium",
    "example": "cmake --build --preset windows-vcpkg"
  }
]

- Presets can be managed via GitHub with mcp_github_create_or_update_file.

